node.title: Latest: NZ records three more Omicron cases, death linked to vaccine
node.content: ["New Zealand has recorded three more cases of the new coronavirus variant Omicron, taking the total number to four in the country.", "The three cases arrived from Dubai last Saturday and are currently in managed isolation and quarantine (MIQ) in Rotorua.", "One of the cases travelled to Dubai from London, another to Dubai from Spain and the third to Dubai from Nigeria, with all three then boarding the same flight to Auckland.", "This comes after New Zealand's first case was reported on Thursday - a person in MIQ, who arrived in Christchurch from Germany (via Dubai and Auckland) about a week ago.\u00a0", "The ministry says that the whole genome sequencing shows that the case was not linked to the first Omicron case reported on Thursday.", "More details will be released in a media statement at 1pm on Saturday.", "A Dunedin man died in November, 12 days after getting his first dose of the Pfizer-BioNTech COVID-19 vaccine.", "Rory Nairn, 26, suffered myocarditis-like symptoms for nearly two weeks before dying, 1 News reports.\u00a0", "It's believed around 0.003 percent of vaccine recipients in New Zealand report myocarditis symptoms, which can be treated, particularly if caught early.", "9:05am -\u00a0Kia ora, good morning, and welcome to Newshub's live coverage of the COVID-19 outbreak for Saturday, December 18."]
